b'Tokenism and Diversity\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
I originally was introduced to joahspearman through joshuakissi last year or so and we vibed immediately. Over the last seven years he\xe2\x80\x99s served as the heart and engine of localeur a company he co-founded that acts as your local intel on the ground as you travel. TripAdvisor it is not lol. This year was the first year I had the chance to participate in an advisory board retreat in Austin with an eclectic mix of individuals from across multiple disciplines.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
One of the early discussions we had over breakfast was this idea of tokenism and its role amidst this idea of diversity. Some brands recognize the underlying social tides are curling hard into one direction and paddling furiously in the general direction to get there figuring out \xe2\x80\x9chow diversity works\xe2\x80\x9d along the way. Others simply go with the flow because they\xe2\x80\x99ve always understood the impact and power of different voices at the table and the outcome of culturally stress-testing ideas.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
If you\xe2\x80\x99re not part of the dominant hierarchy the road is naturally long and difficult. But good ideas exist beyond trends and movements. They form the core of a resilient brand or idea. Seeing Localeur embrace this idea and seeing it applied live and in living color is something unforgettable.\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3

b'If you\xe2\x80\x99ve just met me in recent months and asked what I do for work I probably breezed through it quickly saying I consult or write for beauty brands I host fashion shows for major retailers I travel around the world and write about it or I might have just quipped \xe2\x80\x9cI\xe2\x80\x99m a girl about town! I\xe2\x80\x99ve been doing this for awhile.\xe2\x80\x9d Which is all true but if you dig deeper you\xe2\x80\x99ll find that I damn near killed myself with utter determination and drive to make it as a fashion & beauty editor at major publications (and sacrificed a lot of my sanity!) to get to this point after 14 yrs. I had 7 internships under my belt (including a highly-coveted one at instylemagazine) by the time I graduated college and moved to NYC to launch my glossy magazine career in the Big Apple. \xf0\x9f\x9a\x96 I did a graduate course at Columbia and from there I jumped into the editorial styling world at real_simple before I landed my DREAM JOB in just a few short months at instylemagazine. I pitched and launched a few celebrity style features (remember \xe2\x80\x9cLook for Less\xe2\x80\x9d or \xe2\x80\x9cWhere Can I Find...\xe2\x80\x9d? That was me.) sat next to editorial legends at NY staff meetings networked my heart out and quickly became known as the \xe2\x80\x9cnice editor\xe2\x80\x9d because I always answered PR calls (even on deadline) could never turn down a showroom invite and gave the interns swag when my shelves started to spill over. I came in early and stayed l-a-t-e and I wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t have had it any other way. b"This photo was taken after my first 'spiritual' gig in London about 4 years ago. This is the back of house of the venue it never ceases to amaze me how I'm always surrounded by vintage furniture suitcases and pallets even when I'm talking about Happiness Love and Magick. It seems inevitable I'd start to share what I know about moving home getting organised and feeling safe in The Moving Project.

Helping people feel safe is such an integral part of my work and Ministry. If you don't feel safe it's hard to do anything.  Notice today where you feel safest environment people times of day pay attention and start to spend more time in those places stretching your safety boundaries fuller and richer. Explore the distance between you and your own electric fences what feels good too far out of control. Bring a little smile to your day so you start to dance not tip toe around your personal fence. Change your map.

Find your happy and safe place. This is also a great thing to do with your partner(s) blended roles in the family with kids and fur companions watch body language and you'll learn a lot more about what is feeling good or stretched in yourself and your little or medium ones. 
Bonus thought - know this there's no perfect time for anything. There is now but this is about being present not stressing man made time. 
The soul is limitless and thinks its hilarious we even consider a beginning middle and end to a life within one single century when we are millions of years alive. The body will end  it already ends every 7 years from a cellular point of view  but the soul continues onwards and upwards riding flower filled baskets on bikes to newer and newer adventures."

b"Sound on for my kind of bell bath. In my world we cleanse space with the sound of bells. AND what made this more magick was when we arrived to our new place the church bells rang out. Another blessing for our prosperity and success. 
This wee blue bell is part of a set gifted to me by my mumma when I was 4 years old.

The magick is this - BEFORE you move your belongings into a new home OR when you've organised your current place open all the windows and say your prayers set your intentions and declarations in the house. Then roll your sleeves up and get to cleaning your house wipe down woodwork door handles light switches corners of cupboards. Hoover cobwebs from on high deep clean bathrooms toilets and toilet seats shower curtains and in between tiles. Get the grime gone. Sound obvious but use different clothes for different things. 
Then ring your bell clap your hands beat your drum strum your guitar sing and sound the old out. Itll be grateful to move on to get a promotion and to be free. Remember to welcome new and higher vibration into the space you have made!

The most recent decade of 'spirituality' has 'taught' everyone to clear empty let go but that's only one step. The next part is to fill up with greater energy receive welcome in work cooperatively with energy and magick. If you want to know why your 'spiritual practices' leave you exhausting it's likely because you're focused on emptying yourself and now you are drained as f*ck. No more of that thank you.

Once you've cleaned and rang the bell you can get to casting. More on that very soon.

Big love my movers and dancers. You've got this. AND to everyone moving home and sharing their journey with me thank you! You are doing it. \xe2\x9d\xa4\xf0\x9f\x95\xb8\xf0\x9f\x8f\xb5\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8c\x9f\xf0\x9f\x8c\xbe\xf0\x9f\x95\x8a\xf0\x9f\x92\xab\xf0\x9f\xa4\x97"

b"This is our bedroom right now. We're getting ready to drive the first van load North and pick up the keys! 
This is the most higgledy piggledy part of the process. There's more mess than you know where to start and it all feels like a priority. Some days you just have to say 'feck it' focus on one part of your moving project and nothing else. 
Also dress well. I'm wearing leopard print jeans and gold boots today with accidentally exaggerated eye liner because I wasnt paying attention \xf0\x9f\x98\x82  I'll get james_schock to take a piccy later. 
Everything will get done. Keep breathing. Drink water. Laugh a lot. Have the heart to hearts you need to and don't let anything fester. It can be easy to pick a fight with your partner kids or mates at this stage exhaustion does that. Have a healthy fight if you want to (a what?!) release your passion to get this shit done but do it fairly and in a way which brings you all to peace. 
You cannot control anyone else so let that shite go right now. Hydrate look at the route BEFORE you set off and get your show tunes on. Today is your day.

You've got this."

b"When swans come to you it is a big hello and how do you do.

In Celtic Mythology and many other spirit animal lineages they are about revealing our innate beauty grace and magick. They teach us how to go even deeper into comfort in the darkness to find the golden threads and more. To reveal ourselves.

When they swam to james_schock
And I yesterday I couldn't stop smiling. My devotions have been to reveal and be even more seen. 
I've been removing cloak after cloak since I got here. It's like playing pass the parcel and the gift in the centre is you. Cheesy but delicious. 
Unwrapping and undoing all the knots sticky tape and identity tags until there are no more layers just you or in my case me. Ahhhh there you are you wee beauty. 
Swans are magnificent and they can cause massive damage. Their beaks the claws on their webbed feet if these make contact with human flesh swan 1 - human 0. Also a wing wack is enough to knock you over. 
I love them so much. 
They demonstrate a glorious balance beauty isn't without it's own natural protection. There is cause and effect. There is balance. The energy it takes to hide in plain sight is exhausting and could be used for far more interesting things..such is the way of magick especially Venutian magick swans are her calling card. Venus and I are working together so it made my heart happy to hear from her flock.

I work with a lot of people to undo things ideas which aren't true  perceptions judgements knots contracts in this world and the next it means no two days are ever the same. Heaven on the way to heaven."

b"All of this. When people ask my why I trained as an Interfaith Minister I tell them that I want everyone to experience the celebration of life and death they want. I want the mother to be celebrated and worshipped as much as the idea of a specific type of father has been. I want the mothers who bore everyone and everything to be loved. 
I want the power of the womb to be honoured. The cauldron of creation not specific to gender or genitals.  I want the Goddess known side by side with God. I want everyone to feel really safe and loved. Seen. Held. Known.

I am a daughter of Goddess and God an athlete of the cosmos a winged messenger from gateways and portals and if you cannot yet feel the realness of this know this I don't need you to. Spirit knows.

Mine is a world imagined beyond the realms of 4% grey matter capacity. Mine is a world undefined by a tiny percentage of minds who created a tiny world of 4% human made rhythms.

Ours all of ours is a world of oneness and joy. It is possible. A place of equality hope and enoughness where all are valued.

if this is all too vulgar
to ask in a church
full of men
without milk stains on their shirts

preaching from pulpits off limits to the Mother of God.

but then I think of feeding Jesus
birthing Jesus

onto the soft head of the Salt of the Earth
feeling lonely

loving

and I think

because the real scandal of the Birth of God

All the photos are of my own life taken on my phone nothing fancy just me sharing my world more deeply with you. I read using fancy schmancy stock images and y'all said...Gail we just wanna see ehat you're up to. 
This love letter has evolved as we've talked about it and that's what I adore. Everyone has their own wee favourite bit.

I'll admit sometimes there are spelling errors or typos I miss but you never grudge me that it's always love. And anyway what's a life without typos and wee mistakes here and there?

b"If you haven't met Mr Love-Schock this is he. All round venus in cancer Taurus man of sure footed heart courage and saying yes to adventures. Especially if mud is involved along with hills obstacles and anything to test the mind.

He makes perfect scrambled eggs and cups of tea knows where I am in my cycle and makes me laugh out loud every single day. He embraces all my nature from exploding Celt (day 25) to watery moon (day 29) and everything in between. He's taught me how to feel safe healthily expressing anger dissatisfaction assumption loss. He's one of the few people I fully reveal my joy and freedom to as well. 
This sacred partnership is the deepest curriculum I've learned from and it schools me everyday. If something is missing it's either me or James. We've gone heady not hearty stepped out of the body into wound blame memory need a nap and didn't take it need a snack got influenced by someone else's perception of our relationship it happens. No shame. No judgement. It's all data.We know better how to get back in. Open the front door to Love once more and breathe. Come in. In your home. You are safe.

The Enneagram has been a magnificent tool in our relationship. Educating us in mastering how our personalities show up and how our soul wants to be witnessed. Golden. Challenging at times but what field isn't? We toil for the bounty. Always.

When we first met we were both reading eckharttolle A New Earth which still feels cosmic to us because at the time it was a pretty 'out there' read. We still have both copies.

His personal and work ethic are something else. His loyalty as reliable as a ceremony made with oathing stone or hand fasting ribbons.

The old ones woke me with these whispers....The thing about Love is she opens you sometimes kicks the door down. The divine adult heart can awaken the soul redefining safety pleasure expression desire companionship passion... there is a way to celebrate losing the idea of you in exhange for the truth of you. There is no real loss. It's the sacred work not everyone is prepared to say yes to that school but for those that do there is you Gail. 
The next chapter is emerging."

b"My new obsession is this locket necklace from cultofyouth In fact I love everything she's creating the way she writes shares...it's love in so many different ways.

I remember my first locket as a kid then a teenager with a lock of my boyfriends hair in it then a tiny locket belonging to gran. I dream of finding the perfect locket ring also sometimes known as poison rings pieces of history made modern.

It's interesting for me when it comes to pieces like this 'no grit no pearl' necklace...there are some things I see and dream of opening them as a gift from someone else. It's the idea that someone saw this and thought Gail. An act of love. 
This isn't a pastel sweet tooth nudge or expectation post by the way I don't do hinting. It's more loving than that it's simply something this locket allowed me to feel it allowed me to feel the anticipation of receiving. The ancient art of unhurried waiting. A moment to feel the locket on my own heart bones delicate degrees of linking chain kissing my neck. Delicious. No rush. Sipping life slowly. \xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf"

b"Full Moon Magick. 
I'm not really a big full moon ritual sort of witch. You might be thinking whaaaaat? Well....not in the traditional (whatever that means) sense.

The things I do could be considered mundane I've changed my bedding found the new round pillows of joy (see my stories) for our moon mumma. I've hoovered put the bins recycling out. Took the cat for a walk...yes it's an actual thing now. He runs behind me yelling all the way.  I scattered rose petals and....okay okay there is some ritual but I LIVE in ritual. So maybe what I mean is there's no....AND NOW oh mighty moon grant me blah blah blah give me I shall manifest. Boring! Dull. The moon doesn't want you hitching up your skirts just when she is full and asking her for things like an unpowerful disconnected pretender. Unsexy! 
Why manifest when you can radiate? 
Why pretend when you can live as magick? Why dabble when you can see through your heart eyes as the cosmos not separate from it? 
Why worship one moon when there are thousands connected galactic HUGE. Sexy.

Moon wants you to live with her full new wax wane everything in between. Nothing worse than begging letters at the end of each month. You are more delicious than that. Desperation is the door closing on orgasms of creation.

Look...if you doooooo want to dooooo something it really is all about being I suggest this. Get a piece of paper write your version of what's in my piccy and burn it if you're serious about your life burn your rule book. That one page represents decades of illusion and putting things in the way of love. I did this with a client today and it is MEGA. Please make sure you also say 'the gaps I make with this page burning are filled with gold like butter churning.' Or something similar. Don't empty and not fill with love. Call it to you as you by you in you. If you want to know why you feel drained and fecked when you 'see' certain healers or coaches it's because you deplete and deplete you don't replace with better.

Anyway I promised I'd do the same. So I  burnt my rule book. 
Feels naughty. 
Feels good with a dash of devil if you will. 
Feel free.

Happy moon magick."

b"Sound on please. \xf0\x9f\x95\x8a\xf0\x9f\x95\x8a\xf0\x9f\x95\x8a One of the greatest pleasures in my life is prayer. It's been this way since I was a kid. As has spell writing which is really poetry with purpose as far as I'm concerned.

I've been changing how I respond to requests for prayers because you ask me and I love it. 
I was told to lay a bed of lavender and camomile and to lay down the light to create reflections and support you through collaborative magick.

I kept seeing the candle prayer settings of a church - which by the way if you ever see or hear of any of those beautiful magickal altars of light being available let me know - but for today this is how my prayers look.

You might ask why I don't simply light a single candle. Sometimes I do work with what I call Mother Light or Mother candle a single light for all but today....28 are lit are for those who asked and some for those who didn't ask but need it.

I send you all infinite blessings my loves. Peace and ease. Grace and joy. 
PS that wee green dude of joy is Yoga frog. I love him. He was my gran's. She practised yoga for decades was one of the first people to train in transcendental meditation and she frequently stayed in the many holy Buddhist spaces in Scotland. She spent time with the Dalai Lama and found him she said to be quite lovely. She was the most private of people with deep wells of thought and wisdom and a temper which could flare light a catherine wheel. Volcanic one minute nothing to see the next. We have that in common. I adore her albeit she moved on from her body 39 moons ago."

b"Witch tip of the day. 
To slow yourself and time down brew and make a tea of your choice and stir anti clockwise for as long as you like. Even better stir with your non dominant hand which asks you to pay even more attention. Breath slowly and softly. Full mouth inhale into belly deep exhale through open mouth.  Make sound. Sigh. Empty your lungs. Witness as your body says thank you. \xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf\xf0\x9f\x8d\xaf Whisper I have all the time in the world. As many times as you want. Don't whisper it in a manic tight high pitched crazed way grimacing or clenching convincing yourself it's TRUE. Know it is. \xf0\x9f\x8d\x8e\xf0\x9f\x8d\x8e\xf0\x9f\x8d\x8eThe old ones sang to me this morning of time rituals and seasons undefined by dates other than natures. They asked me to sing my own song the truth is I can hum it but the words are inside my blood somewhere and I can only hold a few at a time. I know I'll remember. \xf0\x9f\x95\xb8\xf0\x9f\x95\xb8\xf0\x9f\x95\xb8 As you slow down what's important is done and your song hums on honey covered lips determined to only say sweet things today.

b"The magick is already in you and all around you. The old ways sing loudly amongst the down pour from the sky this morning. I'm reminded of trusting the weather her winds directions the ones before.

Easy Witch Tip.

Whisper your wish thanks dreams into an apple. No begging prayers please they're not needed. No...if I can just do this or get that or have this then I'll be fine. The old ones don't like it. They don't understand why you martyr yourself for visions of unreal embers shown to you. 
You believe the lies forgot the truth remember they whisper. You are already loved and seen held and honoured full of magick. The forgetfulness disturbs them they believe in you but too long watching you question your heart and they too may believe the lies of you being non magi. Do not shun their faith....whisper from your heart whisper from love begin with simple.cooperative magick. The apple.

Cut the apple across the middle not top to bottom and meet the pentagram. Protection. Amplification. Sacred geometry. Venus.

Personally I eat one half of my wishing apple and bury the second to complete the ritual.

You can also bury or leave by trees return to nature as protection. 
Rituals are with us everywhere an apple a day keeps the doctor away was said by someone with magick."

b"Week two in our new home. 
I'm getting used to the sounds and chirps of the house. Where the light spills the birds sing the smaller winged beauties favour the braches outside this bedroom window the magpies to the front of the house; wood pigeons seeming to permanently fall from twig to twig never really landing. A hurrumph of surprise and fleeing feathers as they pour from one tree  to the next. 
I watched two doves bathe in the rain lifting wings one at a time whilst the other cleaned their warmer feathery nooks. So loving. Gentle. A private moment only seen because I now also live in the branches.

Local church bells ring out hourly. Occasional car sounds join the chorus as a neighbours wheels crunch from car park through private road to loch road.

There is a stillness eye level to tree fingers  I want to climb across an unseen bridge sitting in the heart of these mighty neighbours. A reverends nest beside the rooks and crows.

There are trees in the gardens at least one thousand years in the land. I am a child again when leaning into them chin tilting trying to see through their labyrinth of branches to find their top. Always smiling. These greats guardians are playful and happy.

My mumma rests in the guest room staying for a few days. Familiar at my feet champion snoozer. My beloved husband to join us next week. A family together in branches and song birds. A family together in love."

b"We look superimposed on this piccy BUT it is very real we are full of love and laughter. Our sunsets in Scotland overlooking Gare Loch yesterday afternoon! If we look a bit wired I'll explain..... 4am wake up and go alarms Wednesday to Friday.

Friday night we were loading until after midnight in Worthing.

Another 4am start on Saturday leading to being awake for approx 26 hours into Sunday. Why? Well....I'm going to give you the short version for now. 
We had mighty adventures... We ran out of fuel on the motorway. Sorted thanks to James running 2 miles with a can of diesel.

After the final pit stop and driver change we were on for arriving at approx 5pm making it an easy 12 hour journey.

Nope.

Corinne and I arrived to the magickal new home.My mumma and a friend were there to meet us.Shadow travelled like a boss.

The van broke down 26 miles from our new home at 4.30pm with team James and Libby.

The AA RAC and the company I hired the van from were utter shite but we won't bother about that for now. 
At 2.10am James and Libby arrived home yes 10 hours later.

James Corrine and I started to unload in the dark to find beds bedding etc. Libby (quite rightly) took to Shadow cuddles for soothing and peace.

We finished unloading half the van at 4am.
Shower. Bed. A couple of hours sleep.

Finished unloading Sunday. Met some nrighbours. LOVE them all.

The RAC came to get the van of doom.

Flights and trains arranged for my A Team.
Everyone is fecking wrung out happy and bonded in a way you'll only get if you were there! Or here if you know what I mean.

I'm sitting listening to the local church bells ring out Shadow happy beside me the lounge looking great bedroom ready food in the fridge house toasty feeling happy at having such amazing mighty companions each calm loving solutions focused resilient AF and amazing.

That's the thing about life and moving you can plan for a.lot of things but sometimes an engine will explode and your day will take a different turn. More to follow ky loves but we are safe well and verra happy."
